Rating: 4
My first batch went so quickly, I made some more. The first time I used beautiful, fresh cranberries from an organic farm. They were firm and ripe. This time I only had Oceanspray cranberries in the bag. My recipe came out thinner, as other reviewers have mentioned. I think that the softer, old cranberries make for thinner sauce. I'm going to put it back on the stove to boil off some more of the liquid.

Rating: 4
This is by far the best cranberry sauce I have ever tasted. Everyone at Thanksgiving dinner was impressed. I made the following changes to the recipe. I omitted the bay leaf. I used 5 cinnamon sticks. I added 1 Tbl of candied ginger, chopped. I made this the night before serving. The flavors melded nicely and it was far better the next day, though good out of the pot. I saw no need to add any thickening agent as other reviewers have said. Upon cooling, it was a perfect consistency.

