Rating: 0
I can't rate it because I combined this recipe with the Piquant Cranberry Sauce( Bon App- 11/98). Here's what I did (I know, this is a new recipe...). From this recipe I used: the cranberries, apple cider, cinnamon sticks, cloves and bay leaf (refer to amounts above), then I added 1 cup brown sugar and 2 teaspoons dijon mustard. At the end, I added about 1 tablespoon of honey. It was done in about 20 minutes and the consistency was perfect and the flavor was very good, I couldn't stop eating it!

Rating: 0
I can't rate it because as it was, it was way too tart. But I did fix it up and then it was great. I added 1 c brown sugar, 1/2 c dry white wine, and about 2 tsp corn starch mixed with a couple of Tbsp of water and then boiled several minutes until thickened. It was a BIG hit.

